      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "> OK well in that case I'm fine with adding this. Though extending the existing `~` rule to be more general might still make sense.\r\n\r\nI think the following patch should work for all cases:\r\n```diff\r\n--- a/.gitignore\r\n+++ b/.gitignore\r\n@@ -61,7 +61,7 @@ src/qt/bitcoin-qt.includes\r\n .dirstamp\r\n .libs\r\n .*.swp\r\n-*.*~*\r\n+*~\r\n *.bak\r\n *.rej\r\n *.orig\r\n```",
      "created_at" : "2021-05-12T14:26:03Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/21911#issuecomment-839816871",
